<p>Leonard J. Gordon discovered this remarkable cryptarithm in 1990 &#8212; each letter corresponds to a digit:</p>
<p>NINE &#215; FOUR + FIVE = FORTYONE</p>
<p>9895 &#215; 3074 + 3865 = 30421095</p>
<p>(Leonard J. Gordon, <a href="https://digitalcommons.butler.edu/wordways/vol23/iss2/2/">&#8220;Literary Cryptarithmetic by Computer,&#8221;</a> <a href="https://digitalcommons.butler.edu/wordways/"><em>Word Ways</em></a> 23:2 [<a href="https://digitalcommons.butler.edu/wordways/vol23/iss2/">May 1990</a>], 67-70.)</p>
